	<ThingDef ParentName="AnimalThingBase">
		<defName>AEXP_Anaconda</defName>
		<label>anaconda</label>
		<description>The anaconda is a non-venomous boa species. It is the heaviest and one of the longest known extant snake species, reaching lengths of 5 meters. They are a primarily nocturnal species that tends to spend most of its life in or around water. When prey passes by or stops to drink, the anaconda strikes (without eating or swallowing it) and coils around it with its body. The snake then constricts until it has suffocated the prey.\n\nInterestingly, anacondas have the greatest sexual dimosphism of all land vertebrates, with females sometimes being as much as 4 times the size of males.</description>
		<statBases>
			<MoveSpeed>4</MoveSpeed>
			<MarketValue>775</MarketValue>
			<ComfyTemperatureMin>-20</ComfyTemperatureMin>

		</statBases>
