    <label>indiant elephant</label>
    <description>The Indian elephant, a subspecies of the Asian elephant, is one of the largest unmodified land animals. In general, Indian elephants are smaller, have smaller ears, but relatively broader skulls and larger trunks than African elephants, and have the highest body point on the head.\n\nLike African elephants, the ivory of their tusks has always been considered valuable, a fact that nearly drove them to extinction due to poaching on old Earth.</description>
